channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Team Trump Demands Biden Stop Peddling Charlottesville Lie After Snopes Debunked It
Stefanik touts GOP momentum in blue stronghold, implications for Trump in 2024: 'Democrats have a NY problem'
item.description: House GOP Chair Elise Stefanik spoke with Fox News Digital the implications of Republican momentum in New York for former President Trump in 2024.

item.title: Colorado Dems Push GOP Candidate's Profile in Race for Boebert's Seat
item.description: Colorado Democrats are elevating the profile of a Republican candidate running for the state's 3rd Congressional District ahead of the primary on Tuesday.

item.title: Pro-Hamas Protesters Assault Jews Outside L.A. Synagogue, Clash With LAPD
Biden admin accused of ‘brazen’ attempts to 'weaponize' unionization ahead of election
item.description: The Biden administration came under fire from PLUAC, and top Republicans in the labor union space, over allegations it is politicizing unionization ahead of the election.

item.title: Texas AG Paxton: Biden Always Wanted Noncitizens Voting
item.description: President Joe Biden's plan is to let as many illegal migrants into the country as possible in order to vote, Texas Attorney General Ken Paxton, a Republican, said Sunday.

item.title: Hilarious: Leftist Protesters Heckle AOC and Jamaal Bowman for Not Being Radical Enough
Nevada Democrats sue to keep RFK Jr., Green Party off November ballot
item.description: The Nevada Democratic Party is suing to keep both the Green Party and independent presidential candidate Robert F. Kennedy, Jr. off the November ballot.

item.title: Snopes: Trump Never Called Neo-Nazis 'Very Fine People'
item.description: The lie that then-President Donald Trump called neo-Nazis and white supremacists who attended the 2017 "Unite the Right" rally in Charlottesville, Virginia, "very fine people" was rated "false" by left-leaning fact-checking website Snopes.

item.title: Woke Canada Update: Race-Based Tree Planting in the Name of 'Tree Equity'
Trump's legal team back in court in Florida classified documents case
item.description: Former President Trump's legal team is arguing in court on Monday against the legality of Special Counsel Smith's appointment as well as a gag order against him.

item.title: Gov. Noem Coy on Jan. 6 Pardons
item.description: South Dakota Gov. Kristi Noem dodged the question when asked if she agrees with former President Donald Trump that those who participated in the Jan. 6, 2021, attack on the Capitol should be pardoned, saying that "each of those situations needs to be looked at separately."

item.title: NH Teacher Fired for Calling in Sick to Take Pregnant Student to Abortion Clinic
Exclusive: Trump takes debate prep to campaign trail, calls it a winning strategy
item.description: Former President Trump expressed confidence in his debate prep strategy, dismissing the notion that President Biden could pose a threat onstage in a Fox News interview.

item.title: Fmr WH Physician: Drug Test Biden Before, After Debate
item.description: Rep. Ronny Jackson, R-Texas, a former White House physician during the administrations of Presidents George W. Bush, Barack Obama, and Donald Trump, said he would request that President Joe Biden's physician submit the president to a performance-enhancing drug test.
